      <hedline>
        <hl1>For More Roses</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By PATRICIA JONAS</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Jonas, Patricia</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Removing spent roses helps produce new blooms (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Remove spent roses promptly to help them produce new blooms. Cut back two or three buds to an outward-facing one. Or, with large-flowered varieties, try simply snapping off the flower at the swollen part immediately below the flower stalk.</p>
        <p>Pull off leaves affected by black spot and monitor for powdery mildew.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>Remove spent roses promptly to help them produce new blooms. Cut back two or three buds to an outward-facing one. Or, with large-flowered varieties, try simply snapping off the flower at the swollen part immediately below the flower stalk.</p>
